author: https://www.abc.net.au/news/bridget-brennan/167002
title: Single woman in Poland? Your embryos could be given to another couple
description: Polish laws mean single women with frozen embryos will have to give them up to married couples. It's part of an ongoing war on women by the Polish Government.

author: https://www.abc.net.au/news/annabel-crabb/167108
title: 10 years ago today, Australia's climate change response was thrown into disarray by one man with a plan
description: Ten years ago today, Andrew Robb arrived at Parliament House intent upon an act of treachery. His plan would blow apart Australia's two great parties irrevocably just as they teetered toward consensus on climate change, the most divisive issue of the Australian political century.

author: https://www.abc.net.au/news/jake-sturmer/3572168
title: 'It was desperate': As Hong Kong police advanced, some teens cried, some fled and some stood their ground
description: A high school student who was inside the Polytechnic University during the siege last weekend says it was the most unforgettable experience for the youngsters of Hong Kong.

title: Woman charged with murder after sisters, aged one and two, found dead in car at Qld home 'exposed to extreme heat'
description: A 27-year-old woman has been charged with murder after two young sisters, aged one and two were found unresponsive inside a hot car at Waterford West, south of Brisbane.

title: I thought I was beating the odds but maybe I'm fighting for a future that doesn't exist
description: I worked every minute of the day and dreamed of studying medicine but the more I learn about wealth inequality and social mobility the more see it is probably an impossible goal.

title: 'Once I go back, I will be dead': Chinese spy reportedly seeks asylum in Australia, details covert operations
description: Wang Liqiang is reportedly in an undisclosed location in Sydney on a tourist visa after revealing alleged details of Beijing's espionage activities.

author: https://www.abc.net.au/news/kevin-nguyen/10373694, https://www.abc.net.au/news/danuta-kozaki/7375874
title: 'Lack of humanity': Pregnant Muslim woman speaks out after being punched in cafe
description: Rana Elasmar, who is 38 weeks pregnant, says she fears for the world our children will grow up in after being set upon in a Parramatta cafe in what police suspect was a racially motivated attack.

author: https://www.abc.net.au/news/geoff-lemon/2794678
title: Labuschagne shows ruthless streak at number three in dominant Gabba display
description: Last summer, Marnus Labuschagne resembled a bits-and-pieces Test player — but his ruthless day three display for Australia shows he is growing into a dominant one, writes Geoff Lemon.

title: I fell for a plucky rooster called Percy — and then a card was slipped under my door
description: If you're drawn, inexorably, towards a particularly fine-looking chook, intoxicated with its pizzazz and personality, trust me, it's a rooster and your heart is about to break.

author: https://www.abc.net.au/news/andrea-mayes/5595170
title: Their names are forever linked to a vile crime, but we know very little about Sarah, Jane and Ciara
description: Sarah Spiers. Jane Rimmer. Ciara Glennon. Three women whose names have been etched into Perth's consciousness since the Claremont serial killings 20 years ago.
